.gov/loc.pnp/highsm.69551"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["highsmith, carol m."], "date": "2021-01-01", "dates": ["2021"], "description": ["Title, date, and keywords based on information provided by the photographer. Its base is constructed of steel from the fallen Twin Towers in New York during the terrorist attacks of September 11, 2001. Higgins, a Columbus native, designed and built of the legendary \"Higgins Boats,\" the landing craft with a drop-down front ramp used by troops deployed in Allied forces' D-Day landing assault on entrenched German forces in Normandy, France, and elsewhere. Purchase Carol M. Highsmith Photography, Inc.; 2021  (DLC/PP-2021:107). Forms part of Carol M. Highsmith's America Project in the Carol M. Highsmith Archive. Credit Line: Photographs in Carol M. Highsmith's America Project in the Carol M. Highsmith Archive, Library of Congress, Prints and Photographs Division."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2022-08-02T18:21:48.742Z", "group": ["catalog", "highsm", "catalog-split-08", "main-catalog", "carol-m-highsmith", "main-catalog-split-08"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021757772/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/highsm/69500/69551_150px.jpg#h=150&w=100", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/highsm/69500/69551r.jpg#h=640&w=427", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/highsm/69500/69551v.jpg#h=1024&w=683"], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["nebraska", "platte county", "columbus", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/jpg", "image/tif"], "number": ["2021757772", "2022-06-09t14:48:20", "http://www.loc.gov/item/22637312", "online resource"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["highsmith (carol m.) archive", "catalog", "prints and photographs division", "prints & photographs online catalog (library of congress)"], "score": 36.48132, "shelf_id": "LC-DIG-highsm- 69551"